Both deliverables are written to the bundle directory.

`transcript.json` — schema-validated, 10 iterations, 32 hypotheses, 25 analyses; covers the univariate screen, monotone characterization of `feature_051`, multivariable adjustment, four sets of interaction tests (feature_051 × {013, 067, 011, race, insurance}; 013 × 067; 011 × {013, 067}), demographic-equity probes, the 0-4 ordinal-feature screen, the continuous-biomarker logistic screen, the consolidated full model, and predicted-ORR profiles.

`analysis_summary.txt` — narrative walking through each iteration with effect estimates, p-values, and which hypotheses were supported vs. refuted.

Key signal: `feature_051` (3-level ordinal, monotone ORR 21.1 / 15.7 / 11.0 %) dominates; `feature_011`, `feature_013`, `feature_067` add additive negative effects; `feature_099`, `feature_092`, log `feature_063`, and several binary features (`006/007/039/076/112`) add smaller adjusted effects. No interactions among the top predictors and no race / insurance allocation or efficacy disparities were detectable.
